//biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Solin 1990 134 no.139 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001422\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001422\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 85 no.33 fig.59 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":286,"html":287},"handnote","\u003Cp>Deep v-cut letters with simple terminal serifs. Some letters tending to curved, particularly V, but also tail to F; L and I almost indistinguishable. Simple dash interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  31-32  Line 3-4  28-31  Line 5  22-29  Line 6  15-16 (F tail to 19)  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":289,"html":290},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[292,294,297,298],{"html":293},"Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag",{"id":295,"lang":150,"html":296},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>· d(is) · m(anibus) · \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Asinia Char\n                    mosyne\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Asinia\">Asinia\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Char\n                    mosyne\">Char-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>mosyne\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · v(ixit) · a(nnis) · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>LXV · mens(ibus) · · \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span>